As a reminder to us all, I'm going to hardcode a brief mention of the 5 solas into this welcome section of fellowship

These phrases encompass the core theological convictions of reformed Christianity that distinguish it from other doctrines


--> Sola Scriptura meaning scripture alone. The bible is the sole source of faith and holds authority over church tradition

--> Sola Fide meaning faith alone. Salvation is received by faith, apart from any human works

--> Sola Gratia meaning Grace alone. Salvation is a free gift from God, entirely offered by His grace rather than human effort

--> Sola Christus meaning Christ alone. Jesus Christ is the only mediator between God and man, and salvation is found through only his work on the cross

--> Sola Deo Gloria meaning Glpry to God alone. All glory is due to God alone, salvation is accomplished solely through His will and action




